==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ædˈmɪn.ə.ʃtet.ɚ/ or /-or/}} [[WEAE]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|administrator|administrators}}

# One who [[administer]]s affairs; one who directs, manages, executes, or dispenses, whether in civil, judicial, political, or ecclesiastical affairs; a [[manager]].
#{{Law}} A man who manages or [[settle]]s the estate of an intestate, or of a [[testator]] when there is no competent [[executor]]; one to whom the right of [[administration]] has been committed by competent authority.

